race.comment: WHISTLE WAVE (4) shapes well for this backing up a dominant 19.04 win with success at this track over 340m last time, recording 19.06. Flying lately and expected to go close again. SHREWD ETHICS (5) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind TULSI BANNER (19.17) in a NG. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Leading player again. TULSI BANNER (7) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 19.09 beating SHREWD ETHICS. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. CALYPSO ETHICS (1) scored by 1.5 lengths last time (19.30) in a Grade 4/5 over 340m at this track. Has already won three times from this draw.
